Heat the butter and saut√© the onion gently until just wilted and lightly colored. Add the pepper and cook gently several minutes. Add the celery and tomatoes and bring to a boil. Reduce the heat, add the seasonings, and simmer 12 minutes. Correct the seasoning, add the raw shrimp, and simmer 8 minutes longer or until the shrimp are cooked and blended with the sauce. It is obligatory to serve rice with this dish.